rt-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eparenting%20practices%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20our%20family%3A%20breastfeeding%20through%20toddlerhood%2C%20frequent%20babywearing%2C%20and%20long-term%20bedsharing%20on%20firm%20floor%20mattresses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWatching%20our%20son%20play%20in%20a%20village%20kitchen%20with%3Cem%3E%20dal%20bhat%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fa-holiday-weekend-reminder-that-grilling-is-awesome-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecooking%20on%20a%20wood%20fire%3C%2Fa%3E%20nearby%2C%20I%20marveled%20at%20our%20relatives'%20patience.%20When%20he%20toppled%20a%20shoe%20rack%20for%20the%20third%20time%20in%20five%20minutes%2C%20our%20uncle%20turned%20it%20into%20a%20game%20while%20my%20mother-in-law%20smiled%2C%20unfazed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227360%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mom%20holding%20baby%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fcab2ec9dd4cb81cda8182%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224912%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20says%20her%20parenting%20softened%20in%20India.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20others%20watchful%20of%20his%20safety%2C%20I%20leaned%20back%20with%20tea%20and%20let%20myself%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-i-slowed-down-time-to-enjoy-my-kids-more-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eenjoy%20the%20moment%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F15-ways-to-easily-become-a-better-parent-according-experts-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eparenting%20resource%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20the%20internet.%20Late-night%20searches%20insisted%20my%20son%20should%20sleep%20from%207%20p.m.%20to%207%20a.m.%20with%20two%20daytime%20naps.%20In%20India%2C%20a%20community%20of%20elders%20provided%20guidance.%20They%20encouraged%20me%20to%20trust%20my%20instincts%20and%20follow%20my%20son's%20cues%2C%20not%20the%20clock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20daunting%20at%20first%20%E2%80%94%20one%20day%20he%20took%20three%20short%20naps%2C%20then%20skipped%20the%20nap%20entirely%20the%20next%20morning%20in%20the%20excitement%20of%20taking%20an%20auto%20rickshaw%20to%20a%20cousin's%20for%20brunch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20evening%2C%20as%20we%20took%20aunts%20and%20uncles%20out%20to%20a%20restaurant%2C%20we%20had%20just%20sat%20down%20when%20our%20son%20yawned%20and%20rubbed%20his%20eyes.%20With%20rocking%20and%20humming%2C%20he%20soon%20fell%20asleep%20on%20the%20padded%20bench%20despite%20the%20chatter%20of%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20evening%2C%20I%20rocked%20until%20my%20stomach%20grumbled%20and%20my%20shoulders%20ached%2C%20but%20he%20wouldn't%20settle.%20I%20gave%20in%20and%20let%20him%20play%20with%20pots%20and%20pans%20with%20his%20cousins%20for%20an%20hour%20while%20I%20ate%20dinner.%20My%20tension%20eased%2C%20he%20was%20happy%2C%20and%20he%20later%20drifted%20off%20easily%20on%20his%20own%20timeline.%20Sometimes%2C%20the%20best%20sleep%20trick%20is%20to%20stop%20trying%20so%20hard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20it%20wasn't%20always%20so%20simple%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20still%20couldn't%20let%20go%20of%20tracking%20sleep%20hours%20%E2%80%94%20local%20tips%20boosted%20my%20intuition%20and%20showed%20me%20we%20were%20more%20adaptable%20than%20I'd%20realized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2206bc90de-86f6-4375-b0bd-32f9d140601b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHe%20had%20less%20toys%2C%20but%20more%20people%20to%20play%20with%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20we%20had%20piles%20of%20toys.%20They%20were%20a%20survival%20mechanism%20%E2%80%94%20a%20toy%20airplane%20might%20buy%20me%2010%20minutes%20to%20finish%20dinner%3B%20a%20stacking%20toy%20might%20allow%20me%20to%20drink%20coffee%20while%20it's%20hot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20the%20dynamic%20shifted%3A%20relatives'%20homes%20had%20few%20toys%20but%20many%20playmates.%20Grandparents%2C%20aunts%2C%20uncles%2C%20cousins%20%E2%80%94%20there%20was%20always%20an%20ongoing%20game%20of%20peekaboo%20or%20hide-and-seek.%20I%20didn't%20need%20a%20new%20toy%20to%20get%20a%20moment%20to%20breathe%3B%20I%20just%20needed%20to%20step%20back.%20Our%20son's%20uncle%20played%20with%20him%20while%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20had%20a%20meal%20together.%20A%20neighbor%20watched%20him%20outside%20while%20I%20showered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20returned%20home%2C%20the%20piles%20of%20blocks%20and%20stuffed%20animals%20felt%20suffocating%2C%20prompting%20us%20to%20declutter.%20Then%20we%20finally%20knocked%20on%20our%20neighbor's%20door%20and%20invited%20them%20over%20to%20play%20the%20new%20games%20we'd%20been%20taught.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20learned%20we%20don't%20need%20toys%20to%20survive%20parenthood%20%E2%80%94%20we%20need%20a%20community%20willing%20to%20share%20the%20load.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c3fcf2c8-02e4-4a2a-ba0a-9be73cdf5cab%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EComing%20back%20to%20the%20US%20felt%20lonely%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EComing%20back%20to%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20from%20crowded%20village%20kitchens%20to%20a%20spacious%20living%20room%20with%20no%20one%20to%20fill%20it%20%E2%80%94%20felt%20painfully%20lonely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20lessons%20translate.%20It's%20OK%20to%20ask%20for%20help%20%E2%80%94%20even%20an%20uninterrupted%20meal%20or%20shower%20helps%20me%20reset.%20I%20can%20drop%20a%20routine%20when%20it's%20no%20longer%20working.%20Parenting%20is%20hard%20%E2%80%94%20I'm%20trying%20to%20give%20myself%20grace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20trip%20to%20India%20didn't%20magically%20fix%20everything.%20There%20are%20still%203%20a.m.%20wake-ups.%20I'm%20still%20working%20on%20being%20patient.%20But%20it%20reminded%20us%20of%20what%20matters%20most%3A%20relationships%20with%20our%20son%20and%20the%20people%20we%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20sometimes%2C%20that's%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22htt